title: For Sale:  Nice 9 mm Hi Power
postcontent:
Style: Hi Power
Caliber: 9 mm para (9x19)
HISTORY
Perhaps the most successful military handgun of all time is the Browning High Power. The Browning Hi Power has saved the lives of many allied troops. In terms of sheer numbers the Browning stands alone. The pistol was adopted by over one hundred nations and remains on the front lines in many third world nations as well as a favorite of collectors, shooters and citizens.
Its origins begin with manufacture in Belgium. Among a very few license built copies of the Browning is the FM Browning from Argentina.
Argentina loves the High Power 9 mm – the model that I’m selling.  This started in Argentina in 1937 when the Federal Police ordered Browning High Powers from Fabrique Nationale (FN) in Belgium for its officers.  Later in the 1960's Belgian made High Powers were ordered for Argentine Army officers.
The licensing agreement between Argentina and FN specifically permitted the export of Argentine made High Powers. 
FEATURES
The pistol has a reputation for excellent ergonomics and comfortable to handle as in the tradition of the Browning Hi Power.  The High Power settles into the hand as though it had been custom fitted.  It points naturally, and balances perfectly.
Extremely fun to shoot!  Comfortable, accurate, and have a tendency to make the shooter look good. 
As you might expect, recoil is very manageable.
Sights:  Has the excellent and proven three dot high visibility sights offer a good sight picture and can be acquired quite quickly.
Diamond pattern neoprene grips for a sure fitted feel and nice control.
High capacity magazine included.
Definitely a worthy gun on all counts.

title: For Sale:  Special and rare NORINCO AK !  Check this gem out ! Mak90 NHM90 56S !
postcontent: Very interesting piece of history. This is a de-banned Norinco NHM90 that started life as a pre-ban 56S (Triangle 56 Factory rifle. Polytech Factory). The rifle was caught up in customs at the beginning of the import ban in 1990 hence the birth of the post ban NHM90. (Norinco 56S xxx'd out NHM90) The NHM90's still possessed a threaded barrel that was covered in a barrel cap and came with the hideous thumb hole stock's. This rifle has had the furniture swapped with the correct Chinese wood and the barrel cap has been removed and correct slant brake has been added with the detente pin still intact. Comes with one magazine and original Chinese sling. The rifle was a 56S built rifle and shares the 1.5mm thick receiver and heavy chrome lined barrel. Just like the Mak 90's and Polytech rifles. You will never get closer to the real thing.

postcontent:
CZ P-10 Compact For Sale or Trade. Priced to move quickly.* This is Glock 19 Clone only better.
FEATURES:
Reliable, comfortable to handle and filled with features, CZ's P-10 Centerfire Pistols feel right at home in your hand and in your holster.
Rugged fiber-reinforced polymer frame with a tough nitride finish stands up to tough conditions.
Cold-hammer-forged barrel teams with tactical metal three-dot sights for increased accuracy.
Striker-trigger mechanism minimizes creep, has a smooth 4-4.5-lb. trigger pull and resets quickly for fast follow-up shots.
Large trigger guard allows you to shoot while wearing gloves. Firing-pin block safety.
Includes a mild palm swell, deep beavertail and three interchangeable backstraps.
 
DESCRIPTION
First order of business, ergonomics. Anyone who’s picked up a CZ 75 for the first time gets it — it just has to feel right in the hand. With the CZ grip angle, the P-10 avoids that ‘brick-in-the-hand’ feeling that has plagued many in the striker-fired genre, allowing it to point naturally. A mild palm swell, deep beavertail and three interchangeable backstraps make the P-10 fit a wide variety of hands as if it were built for them. Because it was.
Next up, trigger. So many striker-fired pistols do many things right, falling short when it comes time to pull the trigger. The P-10’s trigger is designed to minimize creep and stacking, and after initial break-in averages a clean 4.5-5 lbs. pull and rebounds with a short, positive reset — meaning single shots can be meticulously placed while follow-ups are effortless.
Built to withstand the rigors of military use, its fiber-reinforced polymer frame and hardy nitride finish are made for the daily grind. A generous trigger guard allows use with gloved hands while being undercut to allow as high a grip as possible, and a set of metal tactical 3-dot sights allow for one-handed manipulation of the slide on a belt.
Like all CZ pistols, the P-10 is built with our legendary cold hammer forged barrel. The ‘C’ in the name indicates that it is compact in both frame and slide size, and magazines are of the same family as the hammer-fired P-07, meaning the P-10 C holds 15+1 in 9 mm in a flush-fitting mag with extended bases allowing 17+1. Take-down of the P-10 will be familiar to most fans of striker-fired guns, and even more pleasing will be holster compatibility with some of the most common guns on the market.

MAGAZINE CAPACITY: 15+1
SIGHTS: METAL THREE-DOT
BARREL: COLD HAMMER FORGED
BARREL LENGTH 4.02 IN
HEIGHT 5.2 IN
WIDTH 1.26 IN
WEIGHT 26 OZ
OVERALL LENGTH 7.3 IN
SAFETY: FIRING PIN BLOCK SAFETY, TRIGGER SAFETY

title: For Sale:  Rast & Gasser M1898 Revolver - WW1 Production - Original Holster and Ammo - rare
postcontent: M1898 Revolver made by Rast & Gasser of Austria-Hungary. The revolver was made in 1915. A true World War 1 production and very neat antique. Only 20,000 M1898 revolvers were made during WW1, so it's a fairly rare pistol. No import mark anywhere, this was surely brought back by a member of the US military after WW1 ended. These revolvers were issued to Austro-Hungarian NCOs, Officers, and machinegunners to use as a sidearm during the war. An extremely cool piece of history. Shoots 8mm Gasser. The revolver is in pretty good condition for being 103 years old. Patina is all original, never messed with in any way. All matching numbers. Also comes with an original WW1 production (STS) Austro-Hungarian holster and 40 rounds of 8mm Gasser ammo. Ammo is newer Fiocchi production. If you're interested, contact me at 419 - five one six - 7735. I can send more pictures if needed. Not entirely sure on its worth, just looking for best offer.
